Myself and many friends are trying no spend January for food and groceries!!

Trying to use as much stuff we have stockpiled for meals , great way to use up older stock .

Our house is d a family of 4 !!

Spend $33.61 today for: bread, yogurt &  eggs (2 bread, 18 eggs, 4  yogurt that’s 630 grams & 14 Yop ) … plus the other day (milk & coffee creamer) , we are at $41.36 so far for groceries this month . Trying to spend as little as possible.

Family of 4, breakfast , kids take lunch to school , supper & snacks . 

Suppers haven been macaroni with ground beef , bacon wrapped scallops with salad , lobster Mac & cheese , turkey bowls (turkey/peas/corn/potatoes/gravy/cheese) , shrimp /sweet potato fries / cucumber/baby tomatoes) , omelettes back bacon .

Kids using their thermos’s for school lunches has been great to use up canned goods . Mother had various seafood in her freezer no one else was going to use so I took it (thus so much seafood) 

Anyone else trying something similar!  #nospendchallenge #nospend #nospendgrocerychallenge #nospendgroceryweek #nospendgroceries

Looking for help !! I volunteer at a local homeless shelter who offers programs to help clients be more successful when housed :) 

Prices of groceries are insane ! Please list in comments any Extremely frugal easy to make recipes. The cheaper they cost the better . Many people after paying rent , etc have less than $200 per month for grocery , personal hygiene items & cleaning supplies. 

I would love to have a months worth of meals that are frugal to print off as a cookbook book or sorts from us to them . 

Can you help ?? Please list in comments:)
